{"TopicId":207298,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Water destroys fps","CreatedByName":"notLily","CreatedById":220175,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-16T22:44:29Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"notLily","CreatedById":220175,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-16T22:44:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am running the game on\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0- Intel core i7-8700\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0- 32gb of 3200mhz ram\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0- Integrated graphics\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0- arch linux\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlying over water causes my fps to drop from 44 all the way down to 17\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022AK41XRC.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002278.42\u0022 height=\u0022775\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/AK41XRC.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-03-16T22:52:29Z\u0022 title=\u002203/16/2022 10:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 16, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by notLily\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAdded Image\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jimmymcgoochie","CreatedById":199902,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-17T13:38:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWater (and terrain) are GPU intensive, you\u2019ll probably get much better FPS with a dedicated graphics card rather than the integrated one you\u2019re using now. If that isn\u2019t an option, turn down reflection and terrain settings and/or just look up unless you absolutely need to see the ground/water as this boosts frame rates quite a lot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"notLily","CreatedById":220175,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-18T21:18:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTerrain isn\u0027t causing any lag for me, its only the water\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-18T21:31:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224104009\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207298\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221647638323\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022220175\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022notLily\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, notLily said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTerrain isn\u0027t causing any lag for me, its only the water\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you using Scatterer with the water settings maxed out?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}